<h1>Dropdown Toggle</h1>

<p class="lead">Show and hide dropdowns.</p>
<p>Use <code>w-dropdown-toggle</code> to make a <a href="/api/havok/widget/DropdownToggle.html">havok/widget/DropdownToggle</a>.

<p>Use a <code>w-dropdown-toggle</code> to wrap a <code>w-dropdown</code> to show/hide the <code>w-dropdown</code></p>

<p>The first child element inside a <code>w-dropdown-toggle</code> is the `button` which will toggle the dropdown. The first <code>w-dropdown</code> child widget inside a <code>w-dropdown-toggle</code> will be toggled.</p>

<h2>With a button</h2>

<div class="bs-docs-example">
    <w-dropdown-toggle>
        <button class="btn">Show Dropdown <b class="caret"></b></button>
        <w-dropdown>
            <a href="http://google.com">Action</a>
            <a href="anotherAction">Another action</a>
            <a href="">Something else here</a>
            <hr />
            <a href="">Separated link</a>
        </w-dropdown>
    </w-dropdown-toggle>
</div>
